entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i wish i could erase the event or seeing my grandmother is funeral which obviously it would not change anything but it was not seeing her there was not something i would wanna like have in my memory

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: she was she was a very positive influence and always was not judgmental and now i mean my parents are great role models just in general i mean they are very successful people so whether or not we have like disagreements or that we are separate people they kind of are good role models in terms of what you wanna have when you are older

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: usually it is easy the problem is staying alseep no matter how late i go to bed whether it is ten pm or four am i will be up like clockwork by seven thirty or eight o clock in the morning the latest every single day and i can not seem to figure out why i cannot stay asleep longer

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are they triggered by something

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i just in the morning i guess i am a lighter sleeper but i just wake up like i just cannot stay asleep anymore which never used to be a problem this consistent but now it is i cannot remember the last time i slept past eight thirty in the morning

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i mean it just makes if i have to do stuff during the day it makes it a lot more tiring but it does not really i am so used to it now it does not really change my mood it is just part of everyday

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not know i kind of just feel very like so so just no extreme highs no extreme lows it is kind of one note land

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i mean nothing like lately like recently it is just i would say over a period of years i have kind of progressively become more seclusive and just reserved and not very outgoing

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have been diagnosed with anxiety

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i had some breathing problems for a day or two and i had to go to the hospital cause i thought it was more serious cause i could not breathe but they said that it was a physical manifestation of my anxiety

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think in the right setting and with the person who is doing it if they are open minded and the therapist is helpful and good at what they are doing then yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you still go to therapy now

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not been to therapy since i was a kid
